    "description": "Meta is seeking a Data Center Infrastructure Management (DCIM) Engineer to become part of our Data Center Facilities Engineering team. Our data centers are the foundation upon which our rapidly growing infrastructure efficiently operates and our innovative services are delivered. The Facilities Engineering team delivers proactive and responsive full-life-cycle engineering expertise to the teams who operate and support our expanding global fleet of data centers.Our Data Center Infrastructure Management System platform enables real-time monitoring and historical analysis of Meta\u2019s global data center footprint through integration and monitoring of the power, cooling, and environmental meters connected to our facilities network. This DCIM Engineering role presents an opportunity to work with related cutting edge technology and to push efficiency and associated performance forward for our downstream partners and the industry.The establishment of new regions in the US, Europe, and Asia are important next steps in the evolution of Meta's infrastructure expansion.\n\nData Center Facilities Engineering, DCIM Engineer Responsibilities:\n\u2022 Lead technically complex DCIM engineering projects for the facilities infrastructure operations team. This includes working cross functionally with other technical organizations including design teams, construction, field operations, vendors and R&D.\n\u2022 Engineering point of escalation for technically complex DCIM system issues that occur in our data centers.\n\u2022 Troubleshoot and engineer enhancements and corrective actions for designs and implementation processes/methods.\n\u2022 Conduct detailed analyses and audits of DCIM system utilization.\n\u2022 Develop effective measurements and reports from Building Management System (BMS) and other monitoring systems to optimize performance and reliability.\n\u2022 Evaluate systems to perform effective and efficient load management and capacity planning. Monitor, trend, and develop engineering metrics and statistical data for strategic planning.\n\u2022 Review new and retrofit DCIM designs, commissioning plans, and critical operational procedures.\n\u2022 Review DCIM \"as-built\" technical documentation and verify accuracy. Investigate actual site conditions and update records.\n\u2022 Develop and generate specifications, RFPs, ROMs and SOWs for projects.\n\u2022 Evaluate facility processes and industry best practices to drive efficiencies and effectiveness.\n\u2022 Routinely report and present to peers, partners and leadership.\n\u2022 Coordination with cross functional partners to ensure DCIM data quality.\n\u2022 Provide DCIM industry expertise in the development of new and enhanced tooling, working closely with end users and cross functional partners.\n\u2022 Develop and maintain processes and procedures associated with the management of the controls and monitoring applications.\n\u2022 Train end users on the proper operation and maintenance of controls and monitoring applications.\n\u2022 Up to 30% travel to data center and vendor sites for engineering studies, on-site technical support, DCIM systems audits, startup testing, and full commissioning.\n\nMinimum Qualifications:\n\u2022 4+ years professional experience in data center engineering, mission critical design, construction, operations, maintenance or related industry.\n\u2022 BS degree in Computer Science, or related field. In lieu of a Bachelor's Degree, either an Associates degree in Engineering (or related Technical School certification) plus 6+ years professional experience or 10+ years of professional experience will be considered.\n\u2022 Troubleshooting and analytical experience.\n\u2022 Experience clearly communicating technical issues.\n\u2022 Possess presentation, project management, and reporting skills.\n\u2022 Experience with computer based mathematical analysis and data analysis.\n\u2022 Experience driving complex projects under pressure.\n\u2022 Experience working independently and as a member of a cross functional team.\n\u2022 4+ years of experience in two or more of the following areas: Electrical Power Monitoring System (EPMS) implementation and support, DCIM evaluation, implementation, and support, BMS implementation and support, Other technical support of electrical and mechanical equipment in a critical facility.\n\u2022 Knowledge of critical facility networking.\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\u2022 Professional experience in data center engineering, mission critical design, construction, operations, maintenance or related industry.\n\u2022 Cross-discipline knowledge of multiple critical facility systems.\n\u2022 Familiarity with industry software tools.\n\u2022 Working knowledge of Building Management Systems.\n\u2022 Knowledge of a variety of commercial DCIM and data center management systems.\n\u2022 Experience with BACnet, Modbus, and OPC-UA communication protocols.\n\u2022 Experience with software programming languages such as Python, PHP, SQL.\n\u2022 Organizational skills and experience beyond the field technician level in activities such as project management, project engineering, and operations management.\n\nMeta is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity and Affirmative Action employer. We do not discriminate based upon race, religion, color, national origin, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, reproductive health decisions, or related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, status as a protected veteran, status as an individual with a disability, genetic information, political views or activity, or other applicable legally protected characteristics. You may view our Equal Employment Opportunity notice here. We also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with applicable federal, state and local law. We may use your information to maintain the safety and security of Meta, its employees, and others as required or per